name: heme-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + hemein = ADP + phosphate + hemeout [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. An enzyme found in Gram-negative bacteria that exports heme.

references.title: Molecular phylogeny as a basis for the classification of transport proteins from bacteria, archaea and eukarya.
orf250 encodes a second subunit of an ABC-type heme transporter in Oenothera mitochondria.
Discovery and sequence analysis of bacterial genes involved in the biogenesis of c-type cytochromes.
